The contract provides for the design and delivery of the Major Project Leadership Academy and other workshops for senior officials to improve the quality of major project leadership in Government. The contract has so far covered:
• Phase 1 (develop and refine the Academy offer in respect of its content, structure and teaching/learning approach, including delivering the first module and designing and running a workshop for Permanent Secretaries and Directors General);
• Phase 2 (delivery of the full Academy offer developed in Phase 1);
• Extended Phase 2 services (which continued the delivery of the full Academy offer and the development and delivery of further workshops for senior officials); and
• Additional Phase 2 services. (These services were provided pursuant to a modification of the contract (as referred to in [Section VII.2.1]).
The modification will extend the contract for the provision of the MPLA which includes delivery of 4 Academy cohorts and 5 additional major project delivery leadership workshops and support activities for the development of senior level civil service capability. The contract will be extended for up to 18 months from 25 January 2021. Over the course of the contract in its entirety (taking into account the proposed modification), the provider will have launched 31 cohorts of MPLA with each cohort taking place over an 18-month period.
